_pTree.descriptionZh: cnschema.org中的CreativeWorkSeries是一组相关项目，通常但不一定是相同的。 CreativeWorkSeries通常按照时间顺序排列。与作为事物列表的通用数据结构的ItemList不同，CreativeWorkSeries的重点在于出版物（例如书籍和期刊，或电视，收音机和游戏等媒体）。特定子类型可用于描述TVSeries，RadioSeries，MovieSeries，BookSeries，Periodical和VideoGameSeries。在每种情况下，可以使用hasPart / isPartOf属性将CreativeWorkSeries与其部件相关联。一般的CreativeWorkSeries类型主要用于组织这些更具体和实用的子类型。适用于该系列的物品的物品通常适用于含有的组。 Schema.org试图预测其中一些案例，但出版商应该可以自由地将系列零件的属性应用于整个系列，无论它们似乎合适
_pTree.rdfs:comment:
A CreativeWorkSeries in cnschema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike ItemList which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as tv, radio and games).

Specific subtypes are available for describing TVSeries, RadioSeries, MovieSeries, BookSeries, Periodical and VideoGameSeries. In each case, the hasPart / isPartOf properties can be used to relate the CreativeWorkSeries to its parts. The general CreativeWorkSeries type serves largely just to organize these more specific and practical subtypes.

It is common for properties applicable to an item from the series to be usefully applied to the containing group. Schema.org attempts to anticipate some of these cases, but publishers should be free to apply properties of the series parts to the series as a whole wherever they seem appropriate.
_pTree.rdfs:label: CreativeWorkSeries

_properties.descriptionZh: 该项的一个附加类型， 通常用于从外部词典中向微数据语法添加更加具体的类型。它表示事物和事物本身所属的类之间的关系。在RDFa语法中, 对多类型最好使用‘typeof’属性这样的本地RDFa语法. Schema.org 工具对额外类型的理解较弱，特别是外部定义的额外类型。
_properties.rdfs:comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
_properties.rdfs:label: additionalType
